                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1091">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/302.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Florida</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallahassee, Fla.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Citizens of Florida now in Mexico City have to-day wired me requesting that I
                    ascertain immediately whether United States will intervene Mexico and give them
                    warning. Such information as you can consistently furnish me will be appreciated
                    for this purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert W. Gilchrist.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
